ðŸ§¾ Revision Notes â€“ B. Fun with Even Subarrays
ðŸ”¹ Problem Summary

You are given an array a of n elements.
You can choose an even-sized subarray of length 2*k and:

for i = 0 to kâˆ’1:
   a[l + i] = a[l + k + i]


â†’ Copy right half onto left half.

Goal:
ðŸ‘‰ Make all elements equal using minimum operations.

ðŸ”¹ Key Observation (Main Trick ðŸ’¡)

Each operation copies right part â†’ left part,
so the last element (a[nâˆ’1]) can be used to make the whole array equal.

Start from the end, and keep expanding the segment of equal elements (same as last value).

ðŸ”¹ Algorithm Steps

Initialize:

target = a[n-1] (last element)

len = 1 (segment length already equal)

ops = 0

While len < n:

If element before this segment (a[n - len - 1]) â‰  target
â†’ perform one operation
â†’ ops++
â†’ len *= 2 (segment doubles)

Else (same value), just extend segment:
â†’ len++

Print total ops.

ðŸ”¹ Intuition

You spread the last element to the left side each time.

One operation doubles the area that is equal to the target.

Stop when the entire array is equal.

ðŸ”¹ Time Complexity

Each step roughly doubles segment size â‡’ O(log n) per test.

Over all test cases: O(t log n) âœ…

ðŸ”¹ Example Walkthrough

Example: a = [4, 4, 4, 2, 4]

Step	len	element checked	same as last?	operation?	new len	ops
1	1	a[3]=2	âŒ	âœ…	2	1
2	2	a[2]=4	âœ…	âŒ	3	1
â†’ All covered						âœ… ans = 1
ðŸ”¹ Edge Cases
Case	Example	Answer	Why
All equal	[1,1,1]	0	Already same
Only 1 element	[1]	0	Nothing to do
All different	[4,2,1,3]	2	Need 2 operations
ðŸ”¹ C++ Code (Final)
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--) {
        int n; cin >> n;
        vector<int> a(n);
        for (int &x : a) cin >> x;

        int target = a[n - 1], len = 1, ops = 0;
        while (len < n) {
            if (a[n - len - 1] != target) {
                ops++;
                len *= 2;
            } else len++;
        }
        cout << ops << "\n";
    }
}

ðŸ§© Summary (1-line)

â€œSpread the last element to the left â€” each operation doubles the equal segment until the whole array matches.â€
